              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The current of the deuteron beam is",
                " approximately 200 uA, and the mean energy of the",
                " deuterium beam is approximately 134 keV. The",
                " experimental tritium titanium target possesses a",
                " thickness of 2.65 mg/cm2. The neutron yield is",
                " (4 - 5) E10 n/s."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The samples were irradiated continuously for",
                " 2 h. After irradiation, the sample cooling time were",
                " 7.6 days for 132Xe and 6.3 - 17.9 h for 134Xe."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " To compensate for variations in neutron flux,",
                " alpha-particles are detected by an Au-Si surface",
                " barrier detector at 135 deg in the direction of the",
                " incoming deuteron beam."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A high-purity germanium (HPGe) detector is",
